  "prompt": "Is Fawad Khan more popular in India?",
  "response": "Fawad Khan, a renowned Pakistani actor, singer, and model, has indeed gained significant popularity in India. His breakthrough in Bollywood came with the 2014 romantic drama *Khoobsurat*, where he played a charming prince, earning widespread acclaim. He further solidified his Indian fan base with his performances in films like *Kapoor & Sons* (2016) and *Ae Dil Hai Mushkil* (2016).\n\nHowever, his popularity in India has faced challenges due to political tensions between India and Pakistan. Following the Uri attack in 2016, the Indian Motion Picture Producers Association (IMPPA) temporarily banned Pakistani artists from working in Bollywood, which affected Fawad Khan's career in the country. Despite this, he retains a strong fan following in India, with many appreciating his acting skills, charisma, and contributions to cinema.\n\nOverall, Fawad Khan remains a beloved figure among Indian audiences, though his presence in Bollywood has been limited in recent years due to geopolitical factors. His work continues to resonate with fans who admire his talent and on-screen presence.",
